  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section id="home" class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1 class="hero-title">Unplug to Reconnect</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Restore your focus. Reclaim your time.</p>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Digital burnout occurs when constant notifications, endless scrolling and
        screen time drain your energy and attention. This campaign helps students
        recognise the signs, reset their habits and rebuild a healthier
        relationship with technology.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#reset" class="btn btn-primary">Start Your Reset Plan</a>
        <a href="#signs" class="btn btn-secondary">Check the Signs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About Section -->
  <section id="about" class="section section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">What is Digital Burnout?</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        Digital burnout is a state of mental fatigue caused by prolonged and
        excessive exposure to screens, fast‑paced content and constant
        connectivity. It can leave you feeling exhausted, distracted, anxious and
        disconnected from real life even when you haven’t done anything
        physically demanding. Our mission is to promote balance: using
        technology mindfully rather than banning it altogether.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Signs Section -->
  <section id="signs" class="section section-pattern">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Recognise the Signs</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        If you relate to several of these warning signs, you may be
        experiencing digital burnout. Awareness is the first step towards
        change.
      </p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Brain Fog</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            You open apps without a clear reason, lose track of time or
            struggle to concentrate even when you try to study.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Tired but Wired</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            You feel exhausted yet your mind stays “on” at night because your
            brain is still stimulated from screens.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Irritability</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Small things annoy you more than usual, especially after long
            scrolling sessions.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Always Checking</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            You feel pressured to respond instantly or fear missing out when
            you’re offline.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Low Motivation</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            You want to start tasks, but scrolling makes real work feel too
            difficult or uninteresting.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Social Draining</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            You chat online all day but still feel lonely or disconnected in
            real life.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reset Plan Section -->
  <section id="reset" class="section section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Reset Your Habits</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        Change doesn’t have to be drastic. Try this simple reset for one week:
        (1) mute non‑urgent notifications, (2) stay screen‑free for the first
        30 minutes of your morning and (3) schedule at least one offline
        activity each day.
      </p>
      <div class="reset-list">
        <div class="reset-item">
          <h4 class="reset-step">Quiet Notifications</h4>
          <p class="reset-desc">Keep only essential alerts so you’re not
            constantly interrupted.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reset-item">
          <h4 class="reset-step">Morning Offline</h4>
          <p class="reset-desc">Spend your first 30 minutes device‑free to
            start calm and focused.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reset-item">
          <h4 class="reset-step">Daily Offline Hour</h4>
          <p class="reset-desc">Read a book, go for a walk, play a sport or
            engage in a creative hobby.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reset-item">
          <h4 class="reset-step">Sleep Reset</h4>
          <p class="reset-desc">Charge your phone outside your bedroom and
            power down screens an hour before bed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stories Section -->
  <section id="stories" class="section section-pattern">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Student Stories</h2>
      <p class="section-text">
        Digital burnout looks different for everyone. Read how fellow
        students overcame it and rediscovered balance.
      </p>
      <div class="story-grid">
        <div class="story-card">
          <img src="gallery/story-1.jpeg" alt="Story 1" class="story-img" />
          <h3 class="story-title">“I couldn’t study without checking my phone.”</h3>
          <p class="story-text">Turning off notifications and keeping the
            phone out of reach made all the difference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="story-card">
          <img src="gallery/story-2.jpeg" alt="Story 2" class="story-img" />
          <h3 class="story-title">“Scrolling at night ruined my sleep.”</h3>
          <p class="story-text">Putting the phone away an hour before bed
            helped restore restful sleep.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="story-card">
          <img src="gallery/story-3.jpeg" alt="Story 3" class="story-img" />
          <h3 class="story-title">“I felt tired even after doing nothing.”</h3>
          <p class="story-text">Replacing 30 minutes of scrolling with a
            sport or walk boosted my energy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

